            <h1>Policy for lifelong learning</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/KD/Temabilder/Kompetansepolitikk/kompetanse_k.jpg" alt="" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">The value of the total human capital in Norway is high, more than six times the value of the petroleum capital. The overall objective for our policy for lifelong learning is to contribute to the best possible management of human capital. </p>
            <img src="/Upload/KD/Temabilder/Kompetansepolitikk/kompetanse_k.jpg" alt="" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>Competence means knowledge and skills used to solve tasks or meet challenges. Compared to the rest of the educational policy, policy for lifelong learning is characterised by a clearer perspective on applicability and working life. Policy for lifelong learning is defined as the unifying policy affecting both development and use of competence in the education system, working life and the rest of society.&nbsp; </p></div>
